   "source": [
    "####     25 Mini Projects with Problem Statements Only\n",
    "Below are problem statements only, no solutions. #####\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Calculator Console App\n",
    "Design a console-based calculator that accepts two numbers and an operator from the user. The program should perform the required arithmetic operation and display the result. It should also handle invalid operator input.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Student Result Generator\n",
    "Create a program that accepts a student’s name and marks in five subjects. Calculate the total marks, average percentage, and grade. Display the result in a formatted report.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Salary Slip System\n",
    "Build a program that takes employee name, basic salary, HRA, DA, and deductions. Calculate gross salary and net salary, then print a salary slip.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. Shopping Bill Generator\n",
    "Develop a billing program that accepts item name, quantity, and price. Calculate subtotal, tax, and total bill amount. Print the final bill in a proper format.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. Age Calculator\n",
    "Write a program that takes a person’s birth year as input and calculates current age. Also print whether the person is a minor, adult, or senior based on age.\n",
    "\n",
    "6. Temperature Conversion Tool\n",
    "Create a tool that allows the user to convert temperatures from Celsius to Fahrenheit or Fahrenheit to Celsius based on menu selection.\n",
    "\n",
    "7. Number Analyzer\n",
    "Build a program that accepts an integer and analyzes whether it is even or odd, positive or negative, divisible by 3, divisible by 5, and whether it falls within a specific range.\n",
    "\n",
    "8. Password Strength Checker\n",
    "Design a password validation tool that checks whether the entered password contains minimum length, uppercase letter, lowercase letter, digit, and special character. Show which conditions passed and failed.\n",
    "\n",
    "9. Email Validator\n",
    "Create a basic email validation tool that checks if the email contains @, ., valid placement of characters, and avoids obvious invalid patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "10. Word and Character Counter\n",
    "Write a program that accepts a sentence or paragraph and prints:\n",
    "\n",
    "total characters\n",
    "total words\n",
    "total vowels\n",
    "total consonants\n",
    "total spaces\n",
    "11. Palindrome Checker\n",
    "Develop a string-based program that checks whether the entered word or sentence is a palindrome after suitable formatting.\n",
    "\n",
    "12. Anagram Checker\n",
    "Create a program that accepts two strings and checks whether they are anagrams of each other.\n",
    "\n",
    "13. Character Frequency Analyzer\n",
    "Build a program that counts the occurrence of each character in a given string and prints the result clearly.\n",
    "\n",
    "14. To-Do List Manager\n",
    "Create a menu-driven to-do list application where the user can add tasks, view tasks, remove tasks, and mark tasks as completed.\n",
    "\n",
    "15. Contact Book\n",
    "Design a contact book using dictionary where the user can:\n",
    "\n",
    "add a contact\n",
    "search a contact\n",
    "update a contact\n",
    "delete a contact\n",
    "display all contacts\n",
    "16. Expense Tracker\n",
    "Build a program that allows the user to enter daily expenses with categories. At the end, show total spending and category-wise expense summary.\n",
    "\n",
    "17. Attendance Manager\n",
    "Develop a system to store student names and whether they are present or absent. The program should print attendance summary including total present and absent.\n",
    "\n",
    "18. Inventory Management Tool\n",
    "Create an inventory system that stores product names, quantities, and prices. Allow user to add products, update stock, and display complete inventory.\n",
    "\n",
    "19. Library Book Tracker\n",
    "Build a menu-based library tracking system where books can be added, issued, returned, and displayed with current availability status.\n",
    "\n",
    "20. Voting Result Counter\n",
    "Create a simple voting application in which votes are stored for candidates. After voting ends, display vote count for each candidate and declare the winner.\n",
    "\n",
    "21. ATM Simulation\n",
    "Design a program that simulates ATM operations such as checking balance, deposit, withdrawal, and mini statement. Prevent invalid withdrawals.\n",
    "\n",
    "22. CLI Calculator\n",
    "Create a calculator that takes command-line arguments using sys.argv. The user should pass two numbers and an operator while running the file.\n",
    "\n",
    "23. CLI Student Report\n",
    "Write a command-line program that accepts a student name and subject marks as arguments, then prints total, average, and grade.\n",
    "\n",
    "24. Number Base Converter\n",
    "Develop a tool that takes a decimal number and displays its binary, octal, and hexadecimal representations. Also allow reverse conversion if you want an extra challenge.\n",
    "\n",
    "25. Multi-Utility Python App\n",
    "Create one menu-driven application that combines multiple tools such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "calculator\n",
    "string analyzer\n",
    "number converter\n",
    "list operations\n",
    "contact book\n",
    "The user should be able to choose one tool from the menu and continue until exit.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  }
 ],
